rawDescription: "one of the most malignant transphobes on this app"
rawContent:
Several months later on April 29, 2021 I was notified out of the blue of an impromptu meeting with my boss and the HR lead on our team at Ubisoft. I want to bring up that the salary I was offered was subpar for my experience and field, especially for the move to a higher cost of living city, but that there was a target bonus promised to everyone on the team that I never received despite working at Ubisoft for over a year (and without which I would not have accepted the job offer). So I actually thought the meeting might be to discuss that, and went into it feeling very excited to finally be getting the full amount of money owed to me.

I was terminated on the spot for "hateful social media comments."

Let me be very clear: This was not a second meeting after an initial meeting where I was told to clean up my social media habits and refused to do so. The first time I even knew my company was spying on and judging my social media posting habits was the second I got fired. And this is a company that worked its hardest to shuffle around sexual harassers: https://t.co/XJqhGzFa8T -- "according to those testimonies, the company protected and promoted known offenders." So @Ubisoft is a company where your career can more easily flourish if you assault women than if you express knowledge of what one is.
